HEADWORD: Tourniquet
<hw>Tour"ni*quet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>tourner</ets> to turn.]</ety> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>An instrument
for arresting hemorrhage. It consists essentially of a pad or compress
upon which pressure is made by a band which is tightened by a screw or
other means.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tournois</ent>⟦br⟧
